1. ABOUT
========
OpenSesame is a graphical experiment builder. OpenSesame provides an easy to
use, point-and-click interface for creating psychological experiments.

2. LICENSE
==========
OpenSesame is freely available under the General Public Licence 3. For the full
license, see the file COPYING in the root of the source tree.

3. INSTALLATION
===============
Binary packages of OpenSesame for Windows, Mac OS, and Linux can be found here:
- <http://osdoc.cogsci.nl/getting-started/getting-opensesame>

Instructions for running OpenSesame from source can be found here:
- <http://osdoc.cogsci.nl/getting-started/running-from-source>

4. DEPENDENCIES
===============
OpenSesame requires (at least) the following packages:
- Python (2.X) <http://www.python.org/>
- PyGame (>= 1.8.1) <http://www.pygame.org/>
- PyQt4 (>= 4.7.4) <http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/pyqt/>
- NumPy (>= 1.3.0) <http://numpy.scipy.org/>

5. CREDITS
==========
OpenSesame includes work of others. All credits go to the respective authors.
(You do not need to install the packages below, as they are included.)

5.1. FONTS
==========
The fonts (resources/*.ttf) are the Droid fonts and
are released under the Apache License 2.0
- <http://www.droidfonts.com/>
- <http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0>

5.2. SOUNDS
===========
The sounds have been taken from the default Gnome sounds and the Kopete instant
messenger sounds. They are released under the GNU General Public License.
- <http://www.gnome.org/>
- <http://kopete.kde.org/>
- <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html>

5.3 ICONS
=========
The icons have been taken from the Faenza and Gnome icon sets. They are released
under the GNU general public license.
- <http://tiheum.deviantart.com/art/Faenza-Icons-173323228>
- <http://www.gnome.org/>
- <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html>
